        <!-- When to Use -->
        <div class="doc-section">
          <h2 id="when-to-use" class="doc-section-title">When to Use</h2>
          <p class="doc-section-subtitle">Use the Text Input component in the following scenarios.</p>
          <ul class="doc-list">
            <li><strong>Single-line text entry:</strong> For collecting short free-text input such as names, emails, URLs, or descriptions.</li>
            <li><strong>Form fields:</strong> As the primary building block for data collection forms across the application.</li>
            <li><strong>Search:</strong> Combined with a prefix search icon for search bars and filter inputs.</li>
            <li><strong>Filters:</strong> In data table toolbars and dashboards for filtering content inline.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <hr class="doc-divider" />

        <!-- Label Position Guidelines -->
        <div class="doc-section">
          <h2 id="label-guidelines" class="doc-section-title">Label Position Guidelines</h2>
          <p class="doc-section-subtitle">Best practices for choosing the right label position across breakpoints and layouts.</p>
          <ul class="doc-list">
            <li><strong>Desktop default:</strong> Always use Label Position = Left. This is the standard layout for desktop forms with sufficient horizontal space.</li>
            <li><strong>Responsive breakpoints:</strong> Auto-switch to Label Position = Top when the viewport width drops below the mobile breakpoint or when the form is inside a narrow container.</li>
            <li><strong>Narrow side panels:</strong> Use Label Position = Top when the text input appears inside drawers, side panels, or modal forms with limited width.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <hr class="doc-divider" />

